## v1.2.0 (2026-06-08)

**Changed by**: ProjectHephaestus PR #1108 (label-event job gating)
**Verification**: verified-ci

**What changed**: Added pitfall #7 "A `pull_request` trigger is workflow-wide — adding
label/auto-merge event types to converge ONE job re-runs EVERY job". Concrete case:
ProjectHephaestus `.github/workflows/_required.yml` added
`labeled, unlabeled, auto_merge_enabled, auto_merge_disabled` to its `pull_request` `types:`
list solely so two lightweight policy jobs (`pr-policy`, `auto-merge-policy`) re-converge on the
PR's true label/auto-merge state — but because the trigger applies to the WHOLE workflow, every
label change re-ran all 18 jobs (full unit+integration matrix py3.10-3.13, security scans, build,
lint). An automation loop toggling `state:*` labels made this very expensive. FIX: a tiny
`changes-gate` job emits `code_event` (true on code events / push where `github.event.action` is
empty, false on `labeled/unlabeled/auto_merge_*`); every heavy job gets
`needs: changes-gate` + `if: needs.changes-gate.outputs.code_event == 'true'`, jobs that already
had `needs: lint` become `needs: [lint, changes-gate]`, and the policy jobs are left UNGATED.
Correctness: a required job SKIPPED via `if:` still reports a neutral/success status and GitHub
keeps the SHA's prior real result, so the `homeric-main-baseline` branch-protection required checks
stay satisfied; `github.event.action` is empty on `push` so the `case` default keeps push-to-main
running everything; `github.event.action` is passed via `env:` (never interpolated into `run:`) for
workflow-injection safety. SELF-TESTED live: after the PR's initial code-event CI, adding then
removing a throwaway label re-ran ONLY changes-gate + the 2 policy jobs (success); the 16 heavy
jobs showed `skipped`; PR stayed CLEAN/MERGEABLE. Added a `## When to Use` trigger, a Quick
Reference row, a detailed `changes-gate` section under Verified Workflow with the YAML and
correctness facts, one Failed Attempts row, a Results & Parameters bullet, an extended `description`
trigger (7), and a ProjectHephaestus Verified On row (PR #1108). Bumped version 1.1.0 → 1.2.0.

